This paper deals with the development of socially-compliant mobile robots, which is a topic that falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of reinforcement learning (RL) and intrinsic motivation, which are subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on human-robot interactions and the use of empowerment as a measure of compliance suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper's application to multi-agent systems suggests that it may also be relevant to the subfield of control systems (cs.SY).
